The recent decision regarding voting preserves the important role of state courts in safeguarding elections and protecting the voice of the American people. However, there is still more work to be done to protect the right to vote and ensure fair representation. The President and the person speaking will continue to fight for access to the ballot box, but they emphasize that Congress also needs to take action. They call on Congress to pass the John Lewis Voting Rights Advancement Act and the Freedom to Vote Act to further protect voters and democracy.